caption: From the moment  you arrive in this restaurant  they give you an excellent feeling. Very courteous crew, it is a happy place to hang out with buddies or with your date. Great  cuisine, professional  chef, comfortable  pay and courteous  service. Warmly recommended.
Had a good experience in this spot with my friend. The food arrived rapidly and the service is just awesome. Prices are fair.

Chicago has tons of great little Mexican restaurants where you can get great cheap food. Buen Apetito is not one of those places. The food is not bad, but the prices are insane. Pico de gallo was pretty bland and watery. They asked me if i wanted my burrito spicy. I of course, said yes. They charged me an extra $.75!! The burrito didn't wind up being all that spicy. If you're in the area, go to the nearby Habanero, a much better and authentic option. I won't be going back.

I wasn't expecting the best mexican food in the world, but this place does not even come close to decent. I got the cheese enchiladas and I've got to say the sauce was probably the worst part. It's not fresh, straight out of the can, you can taste the preservatives and it's not good. Not even spicy. I guess it's partly personal preference, but this dish was not quality by any means. I have not tried their other dishes, but this experience alone makes me never want to go back.

I wish I found this place sooner! No line, but still took a while to make. Why? Because they make it fresh for you while you wait and when you finally get to eat it, it doesn't taste like Chipotle or Qdoba - it tastes like something you can make at home, but spicy, even if you ask for mild! Even though there was lettuce, they don't just use it as filler, every ingredient is wonderfully proportioned and they don't skimp. I'll definitely eat from here again.
I'm eating what is probably the best steak burrito I've ever eaten.  Hands down.  Will be back!
Great Personnel, The Shrimp Quesadillas are to die for.
Good options. Their nachos are huge, the small is enough for one person.
Unexpectedly fresh and delicious food, especially considering the price. Vegetarian friendly as well.

This is a great spot to grab a taco (or 3) for lunch.  Their menu isn't complicted, and they do the 'basic' stuff spot on.  Their chicken or steak tacos are my favorite way to nab a quick cheap-enough lunch on a Tuesday.  As a side note, when they ask if you want your taco spicy, they mean it.  Spicy (it can vary a bit) can occasionally draw a tear or a cough while eating.  Good fun!

While I've enjoyed both the tacos and burritos at Buen Apetito I really have to say that the true standout is the nachos.  I tend to order them as a side when I don't feel a sandwich I brought from home will do the trick on filling me up and both the regular and spicy varieties are always enough to hit the spot! (Honestly I could probably fill up on their small order of nachos most days.)  Their steak is probably the best option to go with though all of their choices are good to pick from!
